
================================================================================
==> Invoking: /some/where/ncrystal
================================================================================
Usage:

  $> ncrystal MODULE <module options>

Here MODULE is the name of a specific command-line module, like "nctool",
"minimc", etc.

Use the -h or --help flag to get information about the options available for a
given module. For example:

  $> ncrystal minimc --help

The full list of available modules are:

  Most important modules:
  =======================

     nctool        : Main tool for investigating materials, files, plugins, etc.
     config        : Access technical info about NCrystal installation.
     minimc        : Investigate multiple scattering and geometry effects via
                     NCrystal's own Monte Carlo simulation framework.

  Modules related to material data conversions:
  =============================================

     cif2ncmat     : Create NCMAT data based on CIF input.
     hfg2ncmat     : Create NCMAT data for amorphous hydrogen-rich materials.
     ncmat2hkl     : Export crystal reflection lists to .laz/.lau formats.
     ncmat2endf    : Export ENDF data (based on endf-parserpy).
     endf2ncmat    : Import ENDF data to NCMAT format (based on PyNE).

  Miscellaneous modules:
  ======================

     vdos2ncmat    : Prepare phonon VDOS data for inclusion in NCMAT data.
     verifyatompos : Verify consistency of atom positions in NCMAT data.
     ncmat2cpp     : Produce C++ code with inline NCMAT data.
     mcstasunion   : Generate McStas-Union code for using NCrystal materials.

